  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nWhy should this feature exist?\r\n\r\nCurrently, using struct `address/hash` will store as 20/32bit (blob) in database which is hard to index and manage. \r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6059935/134796256-c2a74b84-5e24-4325-bf65-45216cc5f370.png)\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6059935/134797581-7ae34281-d899-4b87-8a1f-c50cecf86277.png)\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nDo you have ideas regarding the implementation of this feature?\r\n1. Store address/hash as string rather than []byte.\r\n2. Support Scan() both string and []byte.\r\n\r\nAre you willing to implement this feature?\r\nYes.",
